GIVEAWAY: follow me and @ciatelondon + tag 2 friends and share this on your story to win. There will be 3 winners 🖤.

I picked my favourite products for you to create a full eye look, including a stunning and versatile eyeshadow palette, plus the highlight of my 2020- the dewy blush. The full box is 35£ (RRP 96£), you also get free shipping if you’re from the UK & US. Here’s what’s inside:

Editor Palette Aspen: 18 pan eyeshadow palette with shimmery metals and buttery mattes, a lot of blues and greens but also nudes for a natural look. 

Shadow Flip - Peacock: a multi chrome liquid eyeshadow that shifts into beautiful hues of blue green and purple. This is amazing on a Smokey eye or worn as a liner. 

Mini Wonderwand Liner in Black: super creamy and intense black eye pencil. It’s such a gorgeous consistency, you can easily blend and smudge it. 

Wonderwand Mascara: ultra-black mascara that adds volume and length to your lashes. 

Dewy Blush in Papaya: the most beautiful peach pink tone, the texture is like a balm and it has a gorgeous dewy finish, almost like glass skin.

latestIgtvVideos.title: At home blonde care 🖤
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Since we are in lockdown 2.0 I figured l will share my at home blonde care routine for my blondies out there. My 4 steps routine starts with @redken extreme shampoo which strengthens and repairs weak hair and minimises breakage. I follow that with @kerastase_official blonde absolu masque which is a rich purple mask that removes unwanted yellow undertones. My hairdresser recommended this to keep my blonde hair looking fresh - I use it once a week and it makes my highlights super bright. Before blow drying my hair, I use @redken Playsafe 3-1 treatment that protects hair from heat up to 230C and minimises further breakage. My last step is applying the @kerastase_official elixir oil to seal the split ends and to make my hair shinier and smoother. #ad
 
Shop my favourites on @LookFantastic with 20% off here https://bit.ly/38SsN4R
